"{\"uid\": \"komonews.com-news-local-seattle-home-invasion-robbery-crime-crisis-olympic-hills-husband-wife-dog-police-search-suspects-men-white-black-tall-thin-break-in-facemask-valuables-gun-firearm-violence-ransacking-house-northeast-washington-king-county\", \"text\": \"Now  49\\u00b0  Tue  49\\u00b0  Wed  56\\u00b0  byKOMO News Staff  SEATTLE -Police are searching for three men they say robbed a husband and wife at gunpoint in the early-morning hours Sunday in northeast Seattle.  According to the Seattle Police Department(SPD), the incident occurred around 3 a.m. on the14000 block of 25th Avenue Northeast in the Olympic Hills neighborhood. The husband told officers he was asleep downstairs when his dog woke him up and he heard his wife scream from upstairs, the SPD said. He was then confronted by the suspects, two of whom pointed guns at him and his wife, demanding valuables, the SPD added.  Two of the suspects ransacked the home looking for \\\"anything of value,\\\" and the husband and wife were told not to move before the suspects left, according to the SPD.  The suspects were described as three men between 18 and 25 and 5-foot-10 to 6-1, according to the SPD. Two of the men were Black and one was white, and all were described as tall and thin with black facemasks, black sweatshirts, black pants, gloves and black shoes, the SPD added.  Police said when they arrived to the scene, the couple was \\\"shaken up.\\\"  Police ask anyone with information to call the SPD's violent crimes tip line at206-233-5000.  2025Sinclair, Inc.\"}"